title="Sandwich operators and Einstein deformations of compact symmetric spaces related to Jordan algebras">[hall-2024-sandwich]</fr:link></fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {A}]]></fr:tex> be a (real) normed division algebra. Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathfrak {H}(n,\mathbb {A})]]></fr:tex> be the space of <fr:link
type="local"
href="matrix-0008.xml"
addr="matrix-0008"
title="Hermitian matrix">Hermitian <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n\times  n]]></fr:tex></fr:link> matrices with entries in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {A}]]></fr:tex>. Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathfrak {H}_{0}(n,\mathbb {A})]]></fr:tex> be the subspace of traceless matrices.</fr:p><fr:p>We define the <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Jordan product</html:dfn> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathfrak {H}(n,\mathbb {A})]]></fr:tex> to be:</fr:p><fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[A\circ  B = \frac {1}{2}(AB+BA)]]></fr:tex><fr:p>When <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {A}]]></fr:tex> is associative, this forms a Jordan algebra.</fr:p>
 
   
